quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  51,1,Kasam hai un hawaon ki jo gard (dust) udane wali hain
  51,2,Phir pani se ladeh huey badal uthane wali hain
  51,3,Phir subuk raftari (smoothly speed along) ke saath chalne wali hain
  51,4,Phir ek baday kaam (barish) ki taqseem karne wali hain
  51,5,Haqq yeh hai ke jis cheez ka tumhein khauf dilaya ja raha hai woh sacchi hai
  51,6,Aur jazaa-e-aamal (recompense) zaroor pesh aani hai
  51,7,Kasam hai muttafarriq shakalon(numerous forms) waley aasmaan ki
  51,8,(Aakhirat ke barey mein) tumhari baat ek durse se mukhtalif hai
  51,9,Ussey wahi bargashta (deluded/averse) hota hai jo haqq se phira hua hai
  51,10,Maarey gaye qayas-o-gumaan (conjecturers) se hukum lagane wale
  51,11,Jo jihalat(ignorance) mein garq aur gaflat mein madhosh hain
  51,12,Puchte hain aakhir woh roz-e-jaza kab aayega
  51,13,Woh us roz aayega jab yeh log aag par tapaye jayenge
  51,14,"(Insey kaha jayega) ab chakkho maza apne fitne ka, yeh wahi cheez hai jiske liye tum jaldi macha rahey thay"
  51,15,Albatta muttaqi log us roz baaghon(gardens) aur chashmo (fountains) mein hongey
  51,16,Jo kuch unka Rubb unhein dega usey khushi khushi le rahey hongey. Woh us din ke aane se pehle neikukar (doers of good) thay
  51,17,Raaton(nights) ko kam hi sotey(sleep) thay
  51,18,Phir wahi raat ke pichle peharon mein maafi maangte thay
  51,19,Aur unke maalon(wealth) mein haqq tha saahil( maangne waley) aur mehroom(destitute) ke liye
  51,20,Zameen mein bahut si nishaniyan hain yaqeen laney walon ke liye
  51,21,"Aur khud tumhare apne wajood mein hain, kya tumko soojhta nahin"
  51,22,Aasman hi mein hai tumhara rizq bhi aur woh cheez bhi jiska tumse waada kiya ja raha hai
  51,23,"Pas kasam hai aasmaan aur zameen ke maalik ki, yeh baat haqq hai, aisi hi yaqeeni jaise tum bol rahey ho"